The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Lucknow, Sept. 23 (PTI): The Mayavati government has transferred Uttar Pradesh police chief Vikram Singh, amid strong criticism by Opposition parties of the increasing crime rate in the state.          
	DGP Vikram Singh has been replaced by Karamveer Singh, who has just returned after a central deputation. Vikram Singh had been the DGP since the BSP came to power in 2007.                  
	 Rajahmundry (PTI): A teacher of a school for poor girls has been arrested for allegedly sexually harassing a student during private tuition. Dayasagar had asked the Class IX girl to stay back after tuition on the pretext of taking an extra session. But the girl alleged that he showed her a blue film and tried to force her to do what was being shown in the film. The girl escaped.                  
	 London (PTI): Nalin Surie, an Indian Foreign Service officer, has become Indias high commissioner to the UK. He has taken over from Shiv Shankar Mukherjee, who retired recently. Surie had been serving as the secretary (West) in the foreign ministry prior to the appointment.                  
	 Pittsburgh (PTI): US President Barack Obama has nominated an eminent Indian American agricultural scientist to the post of chief agriculture negotiator. Islam A. Siddiqui is a Uttar Pradesh Agriculture University graduate.                  
	 New Delhi: The Centre is likely to set up two campuses of a proposed central university in Kashmir  one each in Jammu and Srinagar  following protests accusing it of bias against the Valley. HRD minister Kapil Sibal may announce the plan for the twin campuses of the Jammu and Kashmir central university on Thursday, sources said.                   
	 Calcutta: Satyabrata Mukherjee on Wednesday resigned as Bengal BJP president on health grounds. Party sources, however, said Mukherjee was being sidelined following the BJPs debacle in the elections.                                                                                                                           
